en_102547_0	The parliament debate over the removal of Mohan Peries from the post of Chief Justice was held this afternoon as requested by the Opposition.
en_102547_1	The Opposition Leader Nimal Siripala de Silva inaugurated the debate, and leader of the house minister Lakshman Kiriella and several other MP expressed their views.
en_102547_2	Participating in the debate, JVP MP Vijitha Herath said that a presidential commission should be appointed to probe the activities of Mohan Peries.
en_102547_3	The Opposition MPs wore black bands on their arms and staged a protest in the parliament chambers.
en_102547_4	Later the house was adjourned for 10 minutes due to the heated situation in the house.
